ComfyUI FFmpeg Video Combiner
=============================

This custom node combines two video files into one output video using FFmpeg.

Install
-------

1. Put this folder inside `ComfyUI/custom_nodes/`.
2. Install FFmpeg and make sure `ffmpeg` and `ffprobe` are available on PATH.
3. Restart ComfyUI.

Node
----

`Combine Videos (FFmpeg)` appears under `video/ffmpeg`.

Inputs:

- `video_1`: path to the first video.
- `video_2`: path to the second video.
- `mode`:
  - `concatenate`: first video followed by the second.
  - `side_by_side`: both videos next to each other.
  - `top_bottom`: first video above the second.
- `audio`:
  - `first`: use the first video's audio.
  - `second`: use the second video's audio.
  - `mix`: mix both audio tracks when possible.
  - `none`: output silent video.
- `duration`:
  - `longest`: stacked videos continue until the longer video ends.
  - `shortest`: stacked videos end when the shorter video ends.
- `output_filename`: base output filename. A short unique suffix is added so runs do not overwrite each other.
- `width` / `height`: optional target dimensions. Set to `0` for automatic sizing.
- `fps`: output frame rate.
- `crf`: H.264 quality. Lower is higher quality; `18` is visually high quality.
- `preset`: H.264 encoding speed/efficiency preset.

Outputs:

- `output_path`: the generated video path in ComfyUI's output directory.

Notes
-----

Concatenate mode normalizes both videos to the same frame size and frame rate.
If either input has no audio, concatenate mode writes a silent output video.
